Here is a simple JavaScript program that generates and prints ASCII and Hexadecimal values from 0 to 127 (0-7F). 

```javascript
for(let i = 0; i <= 127; i++) {
console.log("ASCII value of " + i + ": " + String.fromCharCode(i));
console.log("Hexadecimal value of " + i + ": " + i.toString(16));
}
```
This program uses a for loop to iterate from 0 to 127 inclusive, and inside the loop it prints out the ASCII character equivalent using `String.fromCharCode()`, and the Hexadecimal representation of each number with `i.toString(16)`. 

The output will be:
```
ASCII value of 0: 0
Hexadecimal value of 0: 0
ASCII value of 1: 1
Hexadecimal value of 1: 1
...
ASCII value of 127: 7F
Hexadecimal value of 127: FF
```
